[% META 
   title = 'Daily Workflow Tutorial - 4-Agent System Guide'
   description = 'Complete step-by-step tutorial for team members on how to execute the daily planning and coordination workflow using the 4-agent system (Daily Audit, DocumentationSync, Master Plan Updater, Daily Plans Generator). Includes agent descriptions, prompt templates, troubleshooting, and team role assignments. Updated Jan 2 with agent lockup prevention fixes.'
   roles = 'admin,developer,devops'
   TemplateType = 'Documentation'
   category = 'workflow,tutorial,agents,planning,team-processes'
   page_version = '0.02'
   last_updated = 'Thu Jan 02 15:46:00 UTC 2026'
%]
[% PageVersion = 'root/Documentation/ai_workflows/DAILY_WORKFLOW_TUTORIAL.tt,v 0.02 2026/01/02 15:46:00 zencoder Exp - Jan 2 Update: Agent lockup prevention protocol documented; multi-file safety constraints added' %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
    [% "Debugging HostName: " _ HostName %]
[% END %]

<div class="app-container">
    <h1>Daily Workflow Tutorial: 4-Agent System Guide</h1>
    
    <div class="alert alert-warning">
        <h3>📋 Purpose of This Guide</h3>
        <p>This tutorial teaches all team members (technical and non-technical) how to execute the daily planning and coordination workflow. The workflow uses 4 specialized AI agents that work together in sequence to maintain project state, update documentation, and generate daily plans for the entire team.</p>
        <p><strong>⏱️ Typical Duration</strong>: 45-90 minutes per day (depending on chat complexity)</p>
        <p><strong>🎯 Best Time</strong>: First thing in the morning, after checking for overnight updates</p>
    </div>

    <div style="background-color: #d4edda; border-left: 4px solid #28a745; padding: 15px; margin: 15px 0;">
        <h3 style="margin-top: 0; color: #155724;">✅ Update: Jan 2, 2026 - Agent Lockup Prevention</h3>
        <p style="margin: 5px 0; color: #155724;"><strong>Multi-File Operations Safety:</strong> Cleanup Agent and other agents now have lockup prevention protocols when updating multiple files. Pattern: /updateprompt BEFORE each file edit (not before all files). This prevents token exhaustion during infrastructure updates.</p>
        <p style="margin: 5px 0; color: #155724;"><strong>Agent Compliance Improvements:</strong> Main Agent spec updated with mandatory /updateprompt enforcement and PATH A/B/C workflow pattern. Ensures consistent behavior across all prompts.</p>
        <p style="margin: 5px 0; color: #155724;"><strong>Impact on Tutorial:</strong> When agents report multi-file operations (like updating 3+ documentation files), they now follow safe checkpoint pattern automatically.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="overview">1. The 4-Agent Workflow Overview</h2>
    
    <div style="background: #f0f7ff; padding: 20px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 20px 0;">
        <h3>How It Works (In Order)</h3>
        <ol style="font-size: 1.1em; line-height: 1.8;">
            <li><strong style="color: #d9534f;">🔴 Daily Audit Agent</strong> - Reads yesterday's work and creates an audit report</li>
            <li><strong style="color: #f0ad4e;">🟠 DocumentationSync Agent</strong> - Updates documentation based on code changes</li>
            <li><strong style="color: #5cb85c;">🟢 Master Plan Updater Agent</strong> - Updates the master coordination document</li>
            <li><strong style="color: #0275d8;">🔵 Daily Plans Generator Agent</strong> - Creates 7-day plans for team execution</li>
        </ol>
        <p style="margin-top: 20px;"><strong>⏱️ Why Multiple Chats?</strong> Zencoder performance degrades with each prompt, so agents run in separate chats with /chathandoff checkpoints between them. This prevents token exhaustion and maintains accuracy.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 id="quick-start">2. Quick Start: First Run of the Day</h2>
    
    <div class="alert alert-info">
        <h4>✅ Morning Checklist (5 minutes)</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Open Zencoder IDE integration</li>
            <li>Navigate to <strong>Chat with AI</strong></li>
            <li>Check today's daily plan: <a href="/Documentation/Daily_Plans-CURRENT-DATE">/Documentation/Daily_Plans-CURRENT-DATE</a></li>
            <li>Run Agent 1 (Daily Audit) - see "Chat 1" section below</li>
            <li>After Agent 1 completes, proceed to Agent 2 in new chat</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <h2 id="detailed-workflow">3. Detailed Workflow: Step-by-Step for Each Agent</h2>

    <h3 id="agent1">Agent 1: Daily Audit Agent (15-20 minutes)</h3>
    
    <div style="background: #fff3cd; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 15px 0;">
        <h4>🔴 What This Agent Does</h4>
        <p>Reads the chat history from yesterday and creates a summary of what was accomplished, what code was changed, and what still needs work.</p>
        <p><strong>Output</strong>: audit_YYYY-MM-DD.md (human-readable) and audit_YYYY-MM-DD.json (computer-readable)</p>
    </div>

    <h4>How to Run Agent 1</h4>
    <table border="1" style="width: 100%; margin: 20px 0;">
        <tr style="background: #f5f5f5;">
            <th style="width: 30%; padding: 10px;">Step</th>
            <th style="width: 70%; padding: 10px;">What to Do</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Open New Chat</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Start a fresh chat conversation (don't use old chats)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Copy Prompt Below</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Use the prompt template (customize placeholders in [BRACKETS])</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Paste & Send</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Send to Zencoder - agent will respond with work summary</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Review Output</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Check the audit files created in Documentation/session_history/audit_logs/</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Wait for /chathandoff</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Agent will execute /chathandoff automatically when done</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <h4>Agent 1 Prompt Template (COPY & PASTE)</h4>
    <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #d9534f; overflow-x: auto;"><code>I need you to run the Daily Audit Agent to document yesterday's work.

Here are the details:
- Yesterday's date: [YESTERDAY-DATE, e.g., 2026-01-02]
- Today's date: [TODAY-DATE, e.g., 2026-01-03]
- Work session: [DESCRIBE YESTERDAY'S FOCUS, e.g., "A.2 K8s Readiness - Phase 2 (Architecture Design)"]
- Chats worked: [CHAT NUMBERS, e.g., "Chats 5-7"]
- Key accomplishments: [2-3 ITEMS, e.g., "Completed K8s architecture design, created migration strategy, tested tooling"]

Run the Daily Audit Agent workflow:
1. Read prompts_log.yaml latest chat entries
2. Extract: files modified, code changes, issues
3. Create: audit_[YESTERDAY-DATE].md (append mode) + audit_[YESTERDAY-DATE].json (merge mode)
4. Generate code diffs for modified files
5. Execute /chathandoff when complete

Note: Output goes to /Comserv/root/Documentation/session_history/audit_logs/</code></pre>

    <h4>What Success Looks Like</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>✅ Agent reads session history and extracts work summary</li>
        <li>✅ Agent creates audit_YYYY-MM-DD.md file (human-readable)</li>
        <li>✅ Agent creates audit_YYYY-MM-DD.json file (structured)</li>
        <li>✅ Agent executes /chathandoff (note in console)</li>
        <li>✅ Agent responds: "Audit complete. Ready for next agent."</li>
    </ul>

    <hr style="margin: 30px 0;">

    <h3 id="agent2">Agent 2: DocumentationSync Agent (10-15 minutes)</h3>
    
    <div style="background: #fff3cd; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 15px 0;">
        <h4>🟠 What This Agent Does</h4>
        <p>Takes the audit from Agent 1 and updates all relevant documentation files. When code changes, this agent finds the corresponding .tt documentation and updates it.</p>
        <p><strong>Input</strong>: audit_YYYY-MM-DD.md (from Agent 1)</p>
        <p><strong>Output</strong>: Updated documentation files in /Comserv/root/Documentation/</p>
    </div>

    <h4>How to Run Agent 2</h4>
    <table border="1" style="width: 100%; margin: 20px 0;">
        <tr style="background: #f5f5f5;">
            <th style="width: 30%; padding: 10px;">Step</th>
            <th style="width: 70%; padding: 10px;">What to Do</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Open New Chat</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Start a fresh chat (previous chat with Agent 1 is done)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Copy Prompt Below</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Use the template with yesterday's date</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Paste & Send</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Agent will sync documentation to code changes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Review Changes</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Agent will list which .tt files were updated</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Wait for /chathandoff</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Agent executes /chathandoff when done</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <h4>Agent 2 Prompt Template (COPY & PASTE)</h4>
    <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #f0ad4e; overflow-x: auto;"><code>I need you to run the DocumentationSync Agent to update documentation based on yesterday's code changes.

Details:
- Audit date: [YESTERDAY-DATE, e.g., 2026-01-02]
- Changed files: [LIST OF CODE FILES MODIFIED, e.g., "Comserv/lib/AI.pm, Comserv/root/static/js/widget.js"]
- Documentation focus: [WHAT TO UPDATE, e.g., "AI Chat System docs, Widget UI/UX docs"]

Run the DocumentationSync Agent workflow:
1. Read audit_[YESTERDAY-DATE].md from session history
2. Map code files to documentation files (e.g., AI.pm → Documentation/controllers/AI.tt)
3. Update relevant .tt documentation files with latest changes
4. Add Recent Changes section noting what was updated
5. Update version numbers and timestamps in META sections
6. Validate all files for HTML/TT syntax
7. Execute /chathandoff when complete

Do NOT create new files; update ONLY existing documentation files.</code></pre>

    <h4>What Success Looks Like</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>✅ Agent reads audit file from Agent 1</li>
        <li>✅ Agent identifies which docs need updating</li>
        <li>✅ Agent updates documentation files (.tt files)</li>
        <li>✅ Agent lists updated files and line counts</li>
        <li>✅ Agent executes /chathandoff</li>
        <li>✅ Agent responds: "Documentation sync complete. Ready for next agent."</li>
    </ul>

    <hr style="margin: 30px 0;">

    <h3 id="agent3">Agent 3: Master Plan Updater Agent (10-15 minutes)</h3>
    
    <div style="background: #fff3cd; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 15px 0;">
        <h4>🟢 What This Agent Does</h4>
        <p>Takes the audit from Agent 2 and updates the MasterPlanCoordination.tt file (the single source of truth for all 15 plans). Updates version numbers, timestamps, status, and next steps.</p>
        <p><strong>Input</strong>: Audit from Agent 1-2</p>
        <p><strong>Output</strong>: Updated MasterPlanCoordination.tt with version bump</p>
    </div>

    <h4>How to Run Agent 3</h4>
    <table border="1" style="width: 100%; margin: 20px 0;">
        <tr style="background: #f5f5f5;">
            <th style="width: 30%; padding: 10px;">Step</th>
            <th style="width: 70%; padding: 10px;">What to Do</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Open New Chat</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Fresh chat (independent from previous agents)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Copy Prompt Below</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Update plan status and next steps</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Paste & Send</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Agent updates master plan file</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Verify Update</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Check <a href="/Documentation/MASTER_PLAN_COORDINATION">/Documentation/MasterPlanCoordination.tt</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Wait for /chathandoff</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Agent executes checkpoint</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <h4>Agent 3 Prompt Template (COPY & PASTE)</h4>
    <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #5cb85c; overflow-x: auto;"><code>I need you to run the Master Plan Updater Agent to update the master plan with yesterday's progress.

Details:
- Audit date: [YESTERDAY-DATE, e.g., 2026-01-02]
- Plans worked on: [LIST OF PLANS, e.g., "A.2 Kubernetes Readiness, E.1 AI Chat System"]
- Status updates: [WHAT CHANGED, e.g., "A.2: Phase 2 Architecture Complete, E.1: Widget Validation In Progress"]
- Blockers: [ANY BLOCKERS, or "None"]
- Next priorities: [TOP 3 ITEMS FOR TODAY, e.g., "Continue A.2 Phase 3, Validate E.1 widget"]

Run the Master Plan Updater Agent workflow:
1. Read MasterPlanCoordination.tt current state
2. Extract current version number
3. Increment version (e.g., 0.12 → 0.13)
4. Update: page_version, last_updated timestamp, Status line
5. Update: Recent Activity section with yesterday's work
6. Update: Next Steps section with today's priorities
7. Validate: HTML/TT syntax correct, dates formatted consistently
8. Execute /chathandoff when complete

File location: /Comserv/root/Documentation/MasterPlanCoordination.tt</code></pre>

    <h4>What Success Looks Like</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>✅ Agent reads current master plan state</li>
        <li>✅ Agent increments version number</li>
        <li>✅ Agent updates timestamp to current date/time</li>
        <li>✅ Agent updates Status section with plan progress</li>
        <li>✅ Agent updates Recent Activity and Next Steps</li>
        <li>✅ Agent executes /chathandoff</li>
        <li>✅ Agent responds: "Master plan updated to vX.XX. Ready for final agent."</li>
    </ul>

    <hr style="margin: 30px 0;">

    <h3 id="agent4">Agent 4: Daily Plans Generator Agent (15-20 minutes)</h3>
    
    <div style="background: #fff3cd; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 15px 0;">
        <h4>🔵 What This Agent Does</h4>
        <p>Takes the updated master plan and creates 7-day daily plans. These plans break down the master plan priorities into actionable daily tasks for the entire team.</p>
        <p><strong>Input</strong>: Updated MasterPlanCoordination.tt from Agent 3</p>
        <p><strong>Output</strong>: 7 new Daily_Plans-YYYY-MM-DD.tt files (one for each day of the week)</p>
    </div>

    <h4>How to Run Agent 4</h4>
    <table border="1" style="width: 100%; margin: 20px 0;">
        <tr style="background: #f5f5f5;">
            <th style="width: 30%; padding: 10px;">Step</th>
            <th style="width: 70%; padding: 10px;">What to Do</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Open New Chat</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Final chat for daily planning</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Copy Prompt Below</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Specify date range for next 7 days</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Paste & Send</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Agent creates 7 daily plan files</td>
        </tr>
        <tr style="background: #f9f9f9;">
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Review Daily Plans</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Check daily plans directory (each plan has navigation)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Wait for /chathandoff</strong></td>
            <td style="padding: 10px;">Agent completes workflow</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <h4>Agent 4 Prompt Template (COPY & PASTE)</h4>
    <pre style="background: #f5f5f5; padding: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #0275d8; overflow-x: auto;"><code>I need you to run the Daily Plans Generator Agent to create 7-day plans for the team.

Details:
- Today's date: [TODAY-DATE, e.g., 2026-01-03]
- Date range for plans: [START-DATE to END-DATE, e.g., 2026-01-03 to 2026-01-09]
- Team focus areas: [TOP PRIORITIES FROM MASTER PLAN, e.g., "A.2 K8s Readiness (main), A.3 Credentials (parallel), B.1/B.2 reviews"]
- Special notes: [ANY CONSTRAINTS, e.g., "Weekend work on Jan 5-6, Holiday on Jan 1"]

Run the Daily Plans Generator Agent workflow:
1. Read MasterPlanCoordination.tt to extract priorities
2. Review previous 7 days of Daily_Plans-YYYY-MM-DD.tt files
3. Calculate next 7-day date range (starting today)
4. Break down master plan priorities into daily actionable tasks
5. Create Daily_Plans-YYYY-MM-DD.tt for each of the 7 days
6. Include: Overview, Priority 1-3 tasks with time estimates, Success criteria
7. Validate all files for HTML/TT syntax
8. Execute /chathandoff when complete

Output: 7 new files in /Comserv/root/Documentation/DailyPlans/</code></pre>

    <h4>What Success Looks Like</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>✅ Agent reads updated master plan</li>
        <li>✅ Agent creates 7 daily plan files (one for each day)</li>
        <li>✅ Agent validates all files are formatted correctly</li>
        <li>✅ Agent updates master plan navigation link to today's plan</li>
        <li>✅ Agent executes /chathandoff</li>
        <li>✅ Agent responds: "Generated 7-day plans. Daily workflow complete."</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 id="team-roles">4. Team Roles & Responsibilities</h2>
    
    <div style="background: #d4edda; padding: 20px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 20px 0;">
        <h3>Who Runs What?</h3>
        <table border="1" style="width: 100%;">
            <tr style="background: #5cb85c; color: white;">
                <th style="padding: 10px;">Role</th>
                <th style="padding: 10px;">Responsibility</th>
                <th style="padding: 10px;">Which Agents?</th>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Daily Workflow Lead</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px;">Initiates all 4 agents in sequence each morning</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px;">Agents 1, 2, 3, 4 (all)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Team Members</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px;">Read generated daily plans; execute tasks for their day</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px;">Daily plans (output from Agent 4)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>Tech Lead / Admin</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px;">Monitor agent execution; troubleshoot issues; update master plan manually if needed</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px;">Can run any agent independently</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="background: #f9f9f9;">
                <td style="padding: 10px;"><strong>DevOps / Infrastructure</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: 10px;">Execute infrastructure tasks from daily plans (K8s, deployments, etc.)</td>
                <td style="padding: 10px;">Reads daily plans for assigned tasks</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </div>

